Basic Cisco Switch Commands
1. Accessing the Switch
Login to switch console

enable — Enter Privileged EXEC mode

configure terminal — Enter Global Configuration mode

2. VLAN Configuration
vlan <vlan-id> — Create VLAN

name <vlan-name> — Name the VLAN

show vlan — Show VLAN configuration and assignments

exit — Exit VLAN configuration mode

3. Port Configuration
interface <interface-id> — Enter interface configuration mode (e.g., interface FastEthernet0/1)

switchport mode access — Set port as access port

switchport access vlan <vlan-id> — Assign port to VLAN

shutdown — Disable interface

no shutdown — Enable interface

4. Viewing Status
show running-config — Show current active configuration

show startup-config — Show saved startup configuration

show interfaces — Show interface status and statistics

show mac address-table — Show MAC address table

5. Saving Configuration
copy running-config startup-config — Save current config to startup config

write memory — Alternate command for saving (older IOS)

6. Assigning IP Address (for management)
interface vlan <vlan-id>

ip address <ip> <subnet mask>

no shutdown — Bring VLAN interface up

7. Resetting and Troubleshooting
reload — Reboot the switch

ping <ip-address> — Test connectivity

show cdp neighbors — Show connected Cisco devices (if CDP enabled)

show arp — View ARP table

8. Miscellaneous
exit — Exit configuration or mode

help or ? — Show available commands/help
